    <p class="desctext">
        
        <span class="tab">A</span> Story About Necromancers is not going to be the title
        of this book, but for now will act as a placeholder do to its accuracy as a descritption. This book revolves around the actions of several necromancers 
        and is told mostly from the perspective of a bard named Anya who has been hired 
        to bear witness to strange happenings in newly conquered lands. Anya is joined 
        by her mysterious employer Saershei and a hired sword known as Olen. The story 
        begins with Anya travelling to meet her new companions and follows throughout 
        their adventures. <br><br>

<span class="tab">Many</span> traditional fantasy elements will be present, things like drinking at a pub or 
inn, magic, swords and fantastic creatures. However the theme is meant to be dark and 
geared more towards feelings of hopelessness. To be certain the theme is meant to be 
dreadful despite the otherwise positive outlook of the main characters. <br><br>

<span class="tab">This</span> book features a female protagonist in a world that is moderately progressive. 
It is an odd mix of children being dutiful to the family, regardless of gender, and a
world where people are free to do what they want; for the most part. Technologically 
the world is consistent with high fantasy ideas, medieval Midgard meets some renaissance,
some steam punk and some technology that should not exist or is magical in nature. <br><br> 

<span class="tab">Religion</span> is present in this world and is mostly based on ancient Indo-European concepts
along with the authorâ€™s creativity. Atheism and not believing in the majority religion
is mostly safe in this world though fanatics do exist. Take Necromancy for example, in 
this world how much religion plays a role in the art varies per practitioner. For some 
necromancers their practice is very devotional while others seek power in order to avoid devotion. <br><br>

<span class="tab">The</span> story takes place in a  nation that is one of many and part of a massive world.
Most borders expand very rapidly leaving most of the internal country in a very wild 
state. This causes travel to be long and dangerous. The rapid expansion is fueled by
nationally sponsored settlement, guild charters or people who are not afraid of a rough
life simply looking for new opportunity.  <br><br>

