        <strong><em>CHARACTERS</em></strong><br><br>
        
        <span class="tab"><strong>Anya:</strong></span><br>
        Newly trained bard, master of lore and highly skilled herbalist.
        Anya is the protagonist in this story and almost everything is told
        from her perspective.With red hair and emerald green eyes she is of
        average height and build. She dresses well, but never with any intention
        to impress, and most of her daily choices are for comfort along the journey.
        
        <br><br>
        <span class="tab"><strong>Saershei:</strong></span><br>
        Mysterious master mage and progenitor of the journey. Saershei is very
        cheerful and extremely friendly. Saershei is tall with raven hair and
        amaranthine eyes that seem to change color often appearing even more
        violet than one would think possible. 
        
        <br><br>
        <span class="tab"><strong>Olen:</strong></span><br>
        Champion sword fighter who is hired by Saershei to guard the party.
        Olen is famous, at least according to Olen, but he is well off enough
        to own two horses so there must be something to his claim. Olen is a
        womanizer, who is taller than most other men, with dark blonde hair.
        Though Olen is a champion sword fighter he does not own any armor,
        except for some leather pieces, and relies on his agility to survive. 
        
        <br><br>
        <span class="tab"><strong>Sonnhilde:</strong></span><br>
        A skilled archer, fighter and magician Sonnhilde has a love for adventure.
        Her dream is to see the world and hopes her wedding to Muruk provides that 
        opportunity. She is the youngest of her siblings, with blonde hair, blue eyes
        and is considered very beautiful. 
        
        <br><br>
        <span class="tab"><strong>Muruk:</strong></span><br>
        Muruk is the son of a noble who has made a name for himself fighting
        in the war with the sea raiders as a ship captain. When the story opens
        he has just been married to Sonnhilde. Muruk is tall with dark hair, very well 
        travelled, creates instant rapport with any one he meets and people 
        are strangely drawn to him. 
        
          <br><br>
        <span class="tab"><strong>Lord-Marshal Drest:</strong></span><br>
        Lord Drest was a great leader in the Exapanse wars and because of his 
        service was awarded a great Citadel on the edge of the Expanse. Lord 
        Drest is one of the most imposing figures you could ever dread to face
        in combat and it is said the orcs of the Expanse viewed him as a 
        physical equal, though that is probably an exageration. 
        
    </p>  

